{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,49],"content":"Compiler Error C2951 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C2951 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,37]}]},{"content":"Compiler Error C2951","pos":[598,618]},{"content":"type declarations are only permitted at global, namespace, or class scope","pos":[619,692]},{"content":"You cannot declare a generic or template class outside global or namespace scope.","pos":[699,780]},{"content":"If you make your generic or template declarations in an include file, make sure the include file is at global scope.","pos":[781,897]},{"content":"The following sample generates C2951:","pos":[904,941]},{"content":"C2951 can also occur when using generics:","pos":[1087,1128]}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error C2951 | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-cpp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"error-reference\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"C2951\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"C2951\"\nms.assetid: c6f95aa2-c894-425b-a51c-d40d70c8daa1\ncaps.latest.revision: 10\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\n---\n# Compiler Error C2951\ntype declarations are only permitted at global, namespace, or class scope  \n  \n You cannot declare a generic or template class outside global or namespace scope. If you make your generic or template declarations in an include file, make sure the include file is at global scope.  \n  \n The following sample generates C2951:  \n  \n```  \n// C2951.cpp  \ntemplate <class T>  \nclass A {};  \n  \nint main() {  \n   template <class T>   // C2951  \n   class B {};  \n}  \n```  \n  \n C2951 can also occur when using generics:  \n  \n```  \n// C2951b.cpp  \n// compile with: /clr /c  \n  \n// OK  \ngeneric <class T>   \nref class GC { };  \n  \nint main() {  \n   generic <class T> ref class GC2 {};   // C2951  \n}  \n```"}